cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for organizing and analyzing unstructured videos of an articulated object class. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves clustering and learning from large amounts of data, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel motion representation and uses a flexible deformation model, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of their system for indexing and retrieval, which could also place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
